<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Difficulty Num=
ber.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>The sample ord=
ers
below indicate the levels of difficulty common</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>to various kin=
ds of
orders (the Difficulty Number is shown in</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>parentheses).<=
/p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>• Easy (5): =
“Prevent
anyone from entering this room.”</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>• Average (9=
):
“Prevent anyone but me from entering this</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>room.”</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>• Hard (15):
