with one terrifying leap, landing on a victim’s</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>back and bruta=
lly
snapping the spine in half. If a molgrim must</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>give chase to
capture its meal, it invariably captures it. Once the</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>creature has t=
he
scent of its prey and sets off in pursuit with an ugly,</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>barking cry, o=
nly
