<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>in fresh water.
Quadrilobes are scavengers, sometimes searching for</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>food alone but=
 often
scuttling across the rocks and sand in groups as</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>large as a doz=
en.
They feed by tearing the flesh of dead animals from</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>the bones using
their wickedly sharp and highly specialized teeth,</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>and a group of
