<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>The vetta’s =
power
waxes and wanes depending on the time of</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>day. During the
early morning, when predators are most active,</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>this power is =
strong
enough to affect any creature that approaches</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>within 20 yard=
s (10
hexes) of a vetta herd. At midday, when the</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>temperature is=
 high
and most predators usually find a shady spot</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>to sleep, the =
power
wanes to almost nothing at 2 yards (1 hex). The</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>power increases
